# Move Freedom Wall & Stories links from Sidebar to Home Feed

## Context
The sidebar has too many links (Home, Explore, Gallery, Freedom Wall, Universe, Stories, Profile, Notifications, Bookmarks, Collections, Settings, Write). The user wants to move **Freedom Wall** and **Stories** out of the sidebar and place them **side-by-side below the search bar** on the main home feed (`PostCards.jsx`).

There's already a "Visit Freedom Wall" button inside the search bar area — we'll replace it with a row of two equal-width pill buttons below the search shell.

## Changes

### 1. `client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/PostCards.jsx`

**Replace** the single `search-freedom-wall-btn` button (line 496-498) and the `mobile-fw-banner` div (lines 579-582) with a new **nav row** placed right after the `</div>` that closes the `search-shell` (after line 577):

```jsx
<div className="search-nav-row">
    <button type="button" className="search-nav-btn search-nav-fw" onClick={handleVisitFreedomWall}>
        <svg ...golden wall icon... />
        Freedom Wall
    </button>
    <button type="button" className="search-nav-btn search-nav-stories" onClick={() => navigate('/home/stories')}>
        <svg ...book icon... />
        Stories
    </button>
</div>
```

- Remove the existing `search-freedom-wall-btn` from inside the search-top-bar
- Remove the `mobile-fw-banner` div (it gets replaced by the new row which works on all sizes)
- Reuse the same SVG icons already used in the sidebar (`Home.jsx` lines 97-102 for Freedom Wall, lines 129-131 for Stories)

### 2. `client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/postcards.css`

- **Remove** `.search-freedom-wall-btn` styles and `.mobile-fw-banner` styles
- **Add** new `.search-nav-row` styles:
  - `display: flex; gap: 6px; padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;` — two equal buttons side by side
  - Each `.search-nav-btn` gets the same pill styling (border-radius, font, size) matching the existing amber Freedom Wall aesthetic
  - `.search-nav-fw` keeps the golden `#e6a817` accent
  - `.search-nav-stories` uses the blue `#5f92ff` accent (matching the existing Stories sidebar icon active color)
  - Mobile responsive: buttons stay side-by-side but shrink slightly at 480px

### 3. `client/src/components/HomePage/Home.jsx`

- **Remove** `freedomWallLink` (lines 91-103) and `storiesLink` (lines 124-132) from the sidebar links arrays
- **Remove** them from both `links` arrays (line 220-221): change from `[homeLink, exploreLink, galleryLink, freedomWallLink, universeLink, storiesLink, ...]` to `[homeLink, exploreLink, galleryLink, universeLink, ...]`

